4. Real Company Scenario Examples
Scenario A: Production Payment Service Down
Symptoms

API returning 500 errors

Response time high

Commands Used
tail -f /var/log/payment-service/app.log
grep -i "timeout" app.log
journalctl -u payment-service -n 100

Root Cause

Database timeout:

ERROR: Connection to DB timed out after 30s

Fix

Restart DB connection pool.

Scenario B: Company Website Very Slow
Commands
grep -i "slow" /var/log/httpd/access_log
tail -n 200 /var/log/httpd/error_log
top
netstat -ntlp

Root cause

Too many connections from one IP.

Fix

Block IP temporarily.

Scenario C: Kubernetes Pod CrashLoopBackOff
Check logs
kubectl logs <pod>

Check previous failed logs
kubectl logs <pod> --previous

Root cause

Misconfigured environment variable.
